5. macro-based typed jobs, if you want less boilerplate

You asked for typed without void *. If the switch boilerplate gets annoying, you can use macros to reduce duplication.

Example:

#define BEAST_JOB_CASE(JOB_ENUM, FIELD, EXEC_FN) \
    case JOB_ENUM: \
        return EXEC_FN(&job->payload.FIELD, job->id)

Then:

static BeastJobResult beastExecuteJob(const BeastJob *job) {
    switch (job->type) {
        BEAST_JOB_CASE(BEAST_JOB_DRAW_GALLERY, drawGallery, beastExecuteDrawGallery);
        BEAST_JOB_CASE(BEAST_JOB_QUEUE_IMAGE_GEN, queueImageGen, beastExecuteQueueImageGen);
        BEAST_JOB_CASE(BEAST_JOB_LOAD_THUMBNAIL, loadThumbnail, beastExecuteLoadThumbnail);
        BEAST_JOB_CASE(BEAST_JOB_DB_WRITE, dbWrite, beastExecuteDbWrite);
        default:
            return beastMakeUnknownJobFailure(job);
    }
}

That keeps typed payloads while reducing repetitive switch code.

